This song means so much to me. Here's the Story why even though no one is gonna read it after 5 years probably.ğŸ˜‚ Some background Information about me. I'm German, 14 years old and I've known him since Collapse, so the 8th of March 2023. The Summer break in Germany ended a couple months ago. In Germany, there are many different types of schools. And when 5th grade starts, it's possible to choose between many different types. I'm in the so-called "Oberschule" which basically translates to high school.  Now it gets interesting: I have a bet with another person that's on a "Gymnasium" which also translates to high school but you have to do more on a "Gymnasium" then on an "Oberschule". Now it gets interesting: The other person I have the bet with is now in 9th grade and her grades are not from this world. In Germany, the grades go from 1 (Neffex aka the best) up to 6 (the absolute worst). On her last Certificate with all the grades she had 8 of these 1s and 6 times one grade below that so a 2. That means she had the best grade possible more often than any other grade. And like I said, I have a bet with her. We're comparing every exam and also the 2 Certificates we're gonna get in this school year and seeing who has the better grades. The one with the better grades wins. And now all the other people suddenly want to talk to me again saying something like: "bro, you had only 2 of these 1s and you want to go up against someone with 8 of these?" "Bro, you're ruining your free time" "Don't you think that's a bit too much?" "Don't you think she's too good for you to beat her?" And soooo much more.  And now, it's my time to Fight Back. I'm gonna edit this Comment after every Exam and every certificate to let y'all know who's winning.  And lastly to everyone somehow seeing this comment and thinking of something that they're doubting to reach or to achieve, this is for you: Hey, I know that you're doubting yourself just as so many other people do. And that's alright. Things feel scary when you first see them. And I've been to that place as well. Do you remember the Covid Pandemic? In these 2 years, my self-confidence didn't exist anymore. I was doubting that I can live another day, that I can stand up, that I can go another step, that I can go another day telling everyone that I'm fine and I'm alright. But after these 2 years I got out of it and I'm motivated to do something every single day. Now I'm not gonna tell you to do something different or try something new, not at all. You can live your life as you want, I have nothing to do with that. But please don't make the same mistake as I did and waste 2 years of your life with these doubts. Thank you and I hope you have a great day or night.â¤
